<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-577-557  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 577 557  OV: 09 577 277.andO; </DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Nov 5 1990 v12 n45 p73(5).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Pagemaker (Mac): version 4.0. (Software Review) (one of sixevaluations of high-end desktop publishing programs) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Assadi, Barbara; Gruman, Galen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Aldus Corp's $795 Pagemaker 4.0 for Macintosh receives an overallrating of 6.8 out of ten placing it towards the top of the sixhigh-end desktop publishing programs evaluated.andP;  Pagemaker is avery good program that a variety of users will find satisfactoryfor uses ranging from manuals and books to newsletters andmagazines.andP;  Pagemaker's drawbacks include weak support provided byAldus, manual manipulation for many layout tasks and graphicscapabilities that include the basics but lack advanced featuressuch as rotation and reversal.andP;  Pagemaker is more than adequate inmost other areas, with particular aptitude for color output.andO;Pagemaker takes advantage of any output device's maximumresolution, and it has support for pantone colors, spot-colorprinting, user-defined colors and four-color separation.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Aldus Corp. (Products).andO;Ticker:    ALDC.andO;Product:   PageMaker 4.0 for Macintosh (Desktop publishing software).andO;Topic:     EvaluationDesktop PublishingSoftware Packages.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>